      "qwen_observation": "Kotlin compiler plugin 1.3.61 fails to compile under JDK 11, producing 'Names _, __, ___, ..., are reserved in Kotlin' error \u2014 the plugin is too old for the target JDK.",
      "qwen_rationale": "The Kotlin plugin 1.3.61 predates JDK 11 support and cannot compile Kotlin sources under JDK 11+. Bumping it to 1.9.25+ before the first JDK 11 step ensures the Kotlin compiler can handle the new JDK. The observation library fix for JDK 21 compatibility is also applied before upgrade_build_to_java21, but the earlier bump is needed to unblock the JDK 11 step where the actual failure occurs."
